Pr\u00edncipe|S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe]]\n|}\n\n== Entities without confirmed cases ==\n\nBelow is a list of countries and territories with no confirmed cases of COVID-19, in order of greatest population.\n\n=== UN member states ===\n\nAs of 5 April 2020, 16 sovereign states (all in [[Africa]], [[Asia]], or [[Oceania]]) have not confirmed any cases of COVID-19. Below is a list of these countries, order by population.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.worldometers.info/geography/alphabetical-list-of-countries/ |title=Population of all countries |work=Worldometer |access-date=23 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323121027/https://www.worldometers.info/geography/alphabetical-list-of-countries/ |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!#!!Country!!Population!!Continent\n|-\n|1||{{flag|Yemen}}||29,825,964||[[Asia]]\n|-\n|2||{{flagicon|North Korea}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in North Korea|North Korea]]||25,778,816||[[Asia]]\n|-\n|3||{{flagicon|Tajikistan}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Tajikistan|Tajikistan]]||9,537,645||[[Asia]]\n|-\n|4||{{flagicon|Turkmenistan}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Turkmenistan|Turkmenistan]]||6,031,200||[[Asia]]\n|-\n|5||{{flag|Lesotho}}||2,142,249||[[Africa]]\n|-\n|6||{{flag|Comoros}}||869,601||[[Africa]]\n|-\n|7||{{flag|Solomon Islands}}||686,884||[[Oceania]]\n|-\n|8||{{flag|Vanuatu}}||307,145||[[Oceania]]\n|-\n|9||{{flag|Samoa}}||198,413||[[Oceania]]\n|-\n|10||{{flag|Kiribati}}||119,451||[[Oceania]]\n|-\n|11||{{flag|Federated States of Micronesia}}||115,030||[[Oceania]]\n|-\n|12||{{flag|Tonga}}||105,695||[[Oceania]]\n|-\n|13||{{flag|Marshall Islands}}||59,190||[[Oceania]]\n|-\n|14||{{flag|Palau}}||18,094||[[Oceania]]\n|-\n|15||{{flag|Tuvalu}}||11,793||[[Oceania]]\n|-\n|16||{{flag|Nauru}}||10,823||[[Oceania]]\n|}\n\n=== Dependent territories ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!#!!Territory!!Population!!Status!!Country!!Region\n|-\n|1||{{flag